abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg tackled issues of racial disparity as he met with Nevada's communities of color Saturday, though the small-town Indiana mayor encountered tough questions and skepticism from some voters.
headline_main: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color

abstract: On a Saturday evening in June 2018, with temperatures in the 70s and the Red Sox playing at Fenway Park, supporters of Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren gathered at the City Winery Boston for a fundraiser.
snippet: On a Saturday evening in June 2018, with temperatures in the 70s and the Red Sox playing at Fenway Park, supporters of Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren gathered at the City Winery Boston for a fundraiser.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On a Saturday evening in June 2018, with temperatures in the 70s and the Red Sox playing at Fenway Park, supporters of Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren gathered at the City Winery Boston for a fundraiser.
headline_main: Warren's Souvenir Wine Bottle Pops Up in Big-Donor Debate
headline_print_headline: Warren's Souvenir Wine Bottle Pops Up in Big-Donor Debate

abstract: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
snippet: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
lead_paragraph: It appears nobody consulted the Jedi Council before scheduling a Democratic debate on the same night that “Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker” opened. So if you missed it, or any of the other happenings on the 2020 campaign trail this week, we’re here to help.

abstract: Violent protests against India's citizenship law that excludes Muslim immigrants swept the country over the weekend despite the government's ban on public assembly and suspension of internet services in many parts, raising the nationwide death toll to 23, police said.
snippet: Violent protests against India's citizenship law that excludes Muslim immigrants swept the country over the weekend despite the government's ban on public assembly and suspension of internet services in many parts, raising the nationwide death tol...
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Violent protests against India's citizenship law that excludes Muslim immigrants swept the country over the weekend despite the government's ban on public assembly and suspension of internet services in many parts, raising the nationwide death toll to 23, police said.
headline_main: 23 Dead as Protests Grow Against India Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: 23 Dead as Protests Grow Against India Citizenship Law

abstract: The California winemakers  who hosted a dinner at a “wine cave” for Democratic presidential hopeful Pete Buttigieg are defending the fundraising event.
snippet: The California winemakers  who hosted a dinner at a “wine cave” for Democratic presidential hopeful Pete Buttigieg are defending the fundraising event.
lead_paragraph: RUTHERFORD, Calif. — The California winemakers who hosted a dinner at a “wine cave” for Democratic presidential hopeful Pete Buttigieg are defending the fundraising event.

abstract: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
snippet: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
lead_paragraph: RUTHERFORD, Calif. — To reach the wine cave that set off a firestorm in this week’s Democratic presidential debate, visitors must navigate a hillside shrouded in mossy oak trees and walk down a brick-and-limestone hallway lined with wine barrels. Inside the room, a strikingly long table made of wood and onyx sits below a raindrop chandelier with 1,500 Swarovski crystals.

abstract: A group of five U.S. senators sent a letter on Thursday to JPMorgan Chase & Co., asking it to explain what it was doing to address what they described as "a troubling list of discriminatory practices" related to race.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — As Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar escalated their attacks on Pete Buttigieg in Thursday night’s Democratic debate, and Mr. Buttigieg forcefully pushed back, a crucial if unspoken fact was driving the political combat: All three candidates are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
